race.comment: Thin maiden to start the day and most of these have had their fair share of chances to break through. NIAMORTAL (6) looks the most progressive horse and is the clear top seed here. He's placed in two of his three starts, including at this track first-up. Drops back 150m but should still be able to settle in the first half dozen. With any natural improvement on last start, he wins this. SIR MONICA (7) has finished midfield in both runs this campaign and might be ready to peak. His form is good enough to measure up here and he looks the main danger, with a gap to most others. GINGERBREAD BOY (1) might be able to run a cheeky race at a price after showing a bit more in a race trial. Stablemates HARLEM GODFATHER (2) and WRATH (8) are worth some thought for exotics.
